  "prompt": "What is the best coffee at Starbucks USA?",
  "response": "The \"best\" coffee at Starbucks can vary based on personal taste, but one of the most popular and highly-rated options is the **Starbucks Reserve\u00ae Cold Brew**. This is made from the company's highest-quality arabica beans and is slow-steeped for 20 hours to bring out the full flavor. Here are a few other favorites that many customers enjoy:\n\n1. **Pike Place Roast** - A well-balanced and smooth medium roast that is a staple at Starbucks.\n2. **Caff\u00e8 Verona** - A dark roast with notes of dark cocoa and caramelized sugar.\n3. **Ethiopia Yirgacheffe** - A light roast with bright citrus and floral notes.\n\nFor those who prefer specialty drinks, the **Flat White** and **Cappuccino** are also highly regarded for their balance of espresso and milk.\n\nFeel free to try a few to see which one suits your taste best!",
